{"info": {"author": "Annotell", "author_email": "Michel Edkrantz <michel.edkrantz@annotell.com>", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# Annotell Authentication\n\nPython 3 library providing foundations for Annotell Authentication\non top of the `requests` library. \n\nBuilds on the standard Oauth 2.0 Client Credentials flow. There are a few ways to provide auth credentials to our api\n clients. Annotell Python clients such as in `annotell-ams`, or `annotell-input-api` accept an `auth` parameter that\n  can be set explicitly or you can omit it and use environment variables. \n\nThere are a few ways to set your credentials in `auth`. \n1. Set the environment variable `ANNOTELL_CREDENTIALS` to point to your Annotell Credentials file. \nThe credentials will contain the Client Id and Client Secret.\n2. Set to the credentials file path like `auth=\"~/.config/annotell/credentials.json\"` \n3. Set environment variables `ANNOTELL_CLIENT_ID` and`ANNOTELL_CLIENT_SECRET`\n4. Set to credentials tuple `auth=(client_id, client_secret)` \n\nAPI clients such as the `InputApiClient` accept this `auth` parameter.\n\nUnder the hood, they all use the AuthSession class which is implements a `requests` session with automatic token\n refresh.    \n```python\nfrom annotell.auth.authsession import AuthSession\n\nauth_session = AuthSession()\n\n# create a requests session with automatic oauth refresh  \nsess = auth_session.session\n\n# make call to some Annotell service with your token. Use default requests \nsess.get(\"https://api.annotell.com\")\n```\n\n## Changelog\n\n### 1.4\n- Add support for `auth` parameter, with path to credentials file or `AnnotellCredentials` object\n- Drop support for legacy API token\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "https://github.com/annotell/annotell-python/tarball/1.4.0", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/annotell/annotell-python", "keywords": "API,Annotell", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "annotell-auth", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/annotell-auth/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/annotell-auth/", "project_urls": {"Download": "https://github.com/annotell/annotell-python/tarball/1.4.0", "Homepage": "https://github.com/annotell/annotell-python"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/annotell-auth/1.4.0/", "requires_dist": ["requests (<3,>=2.20)", "authlib (<1,>=0.14.1)"], "requires_python": "~=3.6", "summary": "Annotell Authentication", "version": "1.4.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Annotell Authentication</h1>\n<p>Python 3 library providing foundations for Annotell Authentication\non top of the <code>requests</code> library.</p>\n<p>Builds on the standard Oauth 2.0 Client Credentials flow. There are a few ways to provide auth credentials to our api\nclients. Annotell Python clients such as in <code>annotell-ams</code>, or <code>annotell-input-api</code> accept an <code>auth</code> parameter that\ncan be set explicitly or you can omit it and use environment variables.</p>\n<p>There are a few ways to set your credentials in <code>auth</code>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Set the environment variable <code>ANNOTELL_CREDENTIALS</code> to point to your Annotell Credentials file.\nThe credentials will contain the Client Id and Client Secret.</li>\n<li>Set to the credentials file path like <code>auth=\"~/.config/annotell/credentials.json\"</code></li>\n<li>Set environment variables <code>ANNOTELL_CLIENT_ID</code> and<code>ANNOTELL_CLIENT_SECRET</code></li>\n<li>Set to credentials tuple <code>auth=(client_id, client_secret)</code></li>\n</ol>\n<p>API clients such as the <code>InputApiClient</code> accept this <code>auth</code> parameter.</p>\n<p>Under the hood, they all use the AuthSession class which is implements a <code>requests</code> session with automatic token\nrefresh.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">annotell.auth.authsession</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">AuthSession</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">auth_session</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">AuthSession</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># create a requests session with automatic oauth refresh  </span>\n<span class=\"n\">sess</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">auth_session</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">session</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># make call to some Annotell service with your token. Use default requests </span>\n<span class=\"n\">sess</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"https://api.annotell.com\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Changelog</h2>\n<h3>1.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Add support for <code>auth</code> parameter, with path to credentials file or <code>AnnotellCredentials</code> object</li>\n<li>Drop support for legacy API token</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7029963, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "d1d0b454e238fdc6cdda21c1000c7ee4", "sha256": "b7cd0b96ccde327170fb6ca4dd9f3fa3908dadd36e952d35a012f8e93caeccee"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "annotell-auth-1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "d1d0b454e238fdc6cdda21c1000c7ee4", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": "~=3.6", "size": 2411, "upload_time": "2020-03-20T09:31:12", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-20T09:31:12.639259Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e5/ba/5bb59cac14acabd721a93c9cc5d0b69c66357d3bc633109e43d068b51938/annotell-auth-1.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "a3f5bf0bbb223